The COD mass balance analysis shows that no major metabolites were omitted in this study (Additional file 2), if considering a reasonable variability error of 10% and that at least 10–12% of the electrons contributed to the production of biomass [25–28]. Nonetheless, the carbon conversion was overestimated in some reactors (10–34%), particularly in the ex-situ biomethanation reactors, being attributed to an endogenous methane production [29]. Although, the inocula were stored at ambient temperature (≅\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
